title: SFH to visit Beijing
content_text:
p>
			The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, will depart for 
			Beijing tomorrow morning (September 12) for a two-day visit. During 
			his visit, he will sign a collaboration agreement with the State 
			General Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and 
			Quarantine (AQSIQ), on the inspection and quarantine of Hong Kong 
			racing horses which will be transported between Hong Kong and 
			Guangzhou. He will also call on the Ministry of Agriculture to

Guangzhou. He will also call on the Ministry of Agriculture to 
			discuss matters of mutual concern. In the afternoon on September 12, Dr Ko will meet the Vice Minister 
			of the AQSIQ, Mr Wei Chuanzhong, to forge closer co-operation and 
			exchange between the two places in food safety as well as inspection 
			and quarantine. The Food and Health Bureau will sign with the AQSIQ 
			the "Collaboration Agreement on Equine Inspection and Quarantine

the "Collaboration Agreement on Equine Inspection and Quarantine 
			associated with the Use of Equestrian Venue after the Guangzhou 
			Asian Games" on the same day. Dr Ko will call on the Vice Minister of Agriculture, Mr Yu Kangzhen, 
			on September 13 to keep himself abreast of the latest prevention and 
			control measures against the avian influenza A(H7N9) virus among 
			poultry on the Mainland. Accompanying Dr Ko on the visit will be the Permanent Secretary for

Food and Health (Food), Mrs Marion Lai; the Controller of the Centre 
			for Food Safety of the Food and Environmental Hygiene Department, Dr 
			Gloria Tam; the Assistant Director of Agriculture, Fisheries and 
			Conservation (Inspection and Quarantine), Dr Thomas Sit; and the 
			Assistant Director of Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation 
			(Fisheries), Dr So Ping-man. Dr Ko will return to Hong Kong in the afternoon on September 13.
